 pad_packed_sequence\nseqs <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.LongTensor([[<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">2</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">3</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">4</span>],[<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">2</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">3</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>],[<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>]])\nseqs <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> Variable(seqs, <span class=\"pl-v\">volatile</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\npacked <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> pack_padded_sequence(seqs, [<span class=\"pl-c1\">4</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">3</span>,<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>], <span class=\"pl-v\">batch_first</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">print</span>(packed.data.volatile)\nseqs_, _ <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> pad_packed_sequence(packed, <span class=\"pl-v\">batch_first</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">print</span>(seqs_.volatile)</pre></div>\n<p>The result is:</p>\n<pre><code>True\nFalse\n</code></pre>\n<p>which is not expected.<br>\nMy environment:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>PyTorch 0.1.12_2, install with conda</li>\n<li>Python 3.5.3</li>\n<li>MacOS</li>\n</ul>", "body_text": "Here's a minimal example:\nimport torch\nfrom torch.autograd import Variable\nfrom torch.nn.utils.rnn import pack_padded_sequence, pad_packed_sequence\nseqs = torch.LongTensor([[1,2,3,4],[1,2,3,0],[1,0,0,0]])\nseqs = Variable(seqs, volatile=True)\npacked = pack_padded_sequence(seqs, [4,3,1], batch_first=True)\nprint(packed.data.volatile)\nseqs_, _ = pad_packed_sequence(packed, batch_first=True)\nprint(seqs_.volatile)\nThe result is:\nTrue\nFalse\n\nwhich is not expected.\nMy environment:\n\nPyTorch 0.1.12_2, install with conda\nPython 3.5.3\nMacOS", "body": "Here's a minimal example:\r\n```python\r\nimport torch\r\nfrom torch.autograd import Variable\r\nfrom torch.nn.utils.rnn import pack_padded_sequence, pad_packed_sequence\r\nseqs = torch.LongTensor([[1,2,3,4],[1,2,3,0],[1,0,0,0]])\r\nseqs = Variable(seqs, volatile=True)\r\npacked = pack_padded_sequence(seqs, [4,3,1], batch_first=True)\r\nprint(packed.data.volatile)\r\nseqs_, _ = pad_packed_sequence(packed, batch_first=True)\r\nprint(seqs_.volatile)\r\n```\r\nThe result is:\r\n```\r\nTrue\r\nFalse\r\n```\r\nwhich is not expected. \r\nMy environment:\r\n- PyTorch 0.1.12_2, install with conda\r\n- Python 3.5.3\r\n- MacOS"}